To send Facebook visitors to your CPA landing page, create a Traffic or Conversions campaign in Meta Platforms Ads Manager.

Step-by-step:
1. Open Ads Manager

Go to Facebook Ads Manager and click Create Campaign.

2. Choose Campaign Objective

Pick one:

Traffic → if you want clicks/visitors.
Sales / Conversions → if you have a pixel and want leads/sales.
Leads → if collecting form submissions.

For CPA marketing, most people start with Traffic.

3. Name Your Campaign

Example:
CPA Offer - USA - Traffic

4. Set Campaign Budget

Choose:

Daily budget: $5–$20/day for testing.
Or Lifetime budget.
5. Create Ad Set

This is where targeting is set.

Website URL:
Put your CPA landing page link.

Audience targeting example:

Country: USA
Age: 25–54
Gender: All / specific
Interests related to your offer

Example:
If promoting weight loss CPA:
Interests = Fitness, Diet, Weight Loss

If promoting finance CPA:
Interests = Credit Card, Loan, Banking

6. Placement

Use Manual Placements first:

Select:

Facebook Feed
Instagram Feed
Stories
Reels

Avoid Audience Network at first (low-quality clicks).

7. Optimization

For Traffic choose:

Landing Page Views instead of Link Clicks.

Better quality visitors.

8. Create Ad

Use:

Attractive image/video
Short headline
Clear CTA

Example:
Headline:
“Claim Your Free Trial Today”

Text:
“Limited-time offer. Click below to get started.”

CTA button:
Learn More / Sign Up

9. Track Results

Watch:

CTR
CPC
CPM
Landing Page Views
Conversion rate in CPA network
10. Scale Winning Ads

If profitable:
Increase budget 20–30% every 1–2 days.

Important for CPA:

Many CPA networks don’t allow direct linking from Facebook.
Use your own landing page/domain first, then redirect to CPA offer.

Flow:
Facebook Ad → Your Landing Page → CPA Offer

This reduces account bans.

Also use Meta Pixel on your landing page for tracking.

This setup is the safest and most effective for CPA marketing.



